ViralBrothers are two friends who create viral videos on social media Their proper names are Petr Melicherík (Erik Meldik) and Jiří Michna (Čeněk Stýblo) Erik Meldik was born on 27 March 1986 in Jeseník. Čeněk Stýblo was born on 15 October 1981 also in Jeseník Erik Meldik studied applied mathematics in economics. Čeněk Stýblo studied English The ViralBrothers channel was founded on September 15, 2011 Earlier work was posted on Stream.cz. Later they founded the SketchBrothers channel together, where they filmed for example the popular series DESATERO Erik Meldik has two children. His older son Anakin (*25.5.2016) and younger daughter Malia (*27.2.2019) Both have previously admitted that they started making videos for a chance to get rich and get famous Erik Meldik has two other YouTube channels. The first is for daily vlogs (ViralBrother Erik - 420k subscribers) and the second is for gaming (ViralErik - 140k subscribers). Cenek Styblo also has his own channel (ViralBrother Cenek - 430 thousand subscribers) Their TikTok account (viralbrothers) has over 2.5 million followers
The first Czech YouTuber to surpass one million subscribers His own name is Jan Macák Born on July 28, 1997 in Pardubice Graduated from high school with a diploma in public relations, marketing and media Published his first video on YouTube at the age of 12 in 2009 His video work focuses on let\'s plays, vlogs and cars In 2021, Forbes magazine ranked him as the third highest paid YouTuber in the Czech Republic with an estimated annual income of CZK 10.5 million His favourite ice cream flavour is vanilla In 2012 he started a second channel called MenTlive, currently called MENTSGARAGE MenT\'s Instagram profile (ment97) has more than 830k followers and contains more than 710 posts
He is one of the most famous, but also the most mysterious Czech YouTubers He has never published his own name or photo He started his YouTube channel GEJMR on November 27, 2011 One million subscribers gained on February 22, 2018 Czech Republic\'s most famous Minecraft YouTuber He has his own Minecraft server called Survival Games. He also runs a YouTuber server called MAJNR Gejmr is an avid stamp collector Forbes ranked him 10th in the 2017 Most Influential Czechs He owns two more channels - GEJMROVEC (297 thousand subscribers) and GEJMR Vlogger (98 thousand subscribers) Gejmr\'s Instagram profile (gejmr) has more than 606k followers and contains more than 200 posts
His video work focuses on let\'s plays, mostly from the game Minecraft, but he also makes vlogs His own name is Petr Hybš (Petr Florián) He graduated from a grammar school and higher vocational school in Pilsen Before YouTube he worked as a photographer He is happily married and has two sons and a daughter His main hobbies are fishing, outdoor camping and music He founded his channel PedrosGame on 5 January 2012 He owns two more channels - Petrův svět (66k subscribers) and Pedro (49k subscribers) He used to own one more channel, but he handed it over to a fan - Adam\'s Life (132k subscribers) Pedro\'s Instagram profile (pedrosgame) has over 516k followers and contains over 894 posts
His work focuses on Pearls of the World, facts about movies and occasionally unpacks interesting products from Wishe . His own name is Jakub Steklý He graduated from the Business Academy High School, then entered the University of Pardubice, which he did not finish He had his own show on the TV station Óčko - Dotykáč, which was about mobile applications He wanted to be an actor or presenter from a young age, and in primary school he performed in the school theatre In 2015, Forbes ranked him 14th on a list of the 77 most influential Czechs on social media His hobby is breaking Czech and international Guinness World Records. He holds the Czech record for the number of weekly vlogs, which he started filming on 13 May 2016, showing things from his personal life, information about future plans and other such things He owns two more channels - Stejk play (102k subscribers) and Tady hraje Stejk (83k subscribers) Bought a blue Mercedes-Benz CLA 2021 Stejk\'s Instagram profile (stejkstudio) has more than 540k followers and contains more than 3710 posts
Former Czech YouTuber and former participant of the reality TV show Nova - Farma (2012) He graduated from high school in Brno, in 2009 he moved to Prague where he worked at Tiscali Media as an ad space administrator Jirka Král ended his YouTube career on 2 September 2018 with his last video documentary (I was a Youtuber [DOCUMENT]) His wife, as of August 27, 2020, is traveler and blogger Karolína Králová (née Benešová), who goes by the nickname Little Kao On 11 February 2018, he reached the 1 million subscriber mark In 2016, Forbes magazine ranked him number one on its 2016 list of the 10 most influential Czechs Due to his popularity, he has interesting collaborations with McDonald\'s, Avast and Red Bull His own burger (BURGER JIRKA KRÁLE) was sold at McDonald's fast food outlet. He had his own comic book, which was first published on 13 May 2016 with a price tag of 39c. A total of 44 issues were published and the comic was finished at the end of 2019 Jirka\'s Instagram profile (jirkakral) has over 920k followers and contains over 1844 posts
His video work focuses on let\'s plays, mostly from the game Roblox, but he also makes motovlogs His own name is Jakub Váňa He graduated from business school He founded his channel MinecraftBox together with his friend Jezisek1 on 5 January 2012, but renamed it to its current name HouseBox on 27 April 2016 In 2021, Forbes magazine ranked him as the 10th highest paid YouTuber in the Czech Republic with an estimated annual income of CZK 4.5 million His favourite colour is red or black He likes to travel, whether on a motorbike or in a plane He bought a white Kawasaki ER 6N House filmed the game Battlefield in 2011 for the Jakub Váňa channel where he had over 500 subscribers House\'s Instagram profile (jakub.house) has over 423k followers and contains over 211 posts
His video work focuses on informative and political videos, but he also makes vlogs or parodies His own name is Karel Kovář He was born in Pardubice. He graduated from high school in 2016 and later that year moved to Prague to study at the Faculty of Social Sciences of Charles University in the field of marketing communications and PR. He completed this study in the third semester. In 2017 he won the Blogger of the Year poll. In 2021, Forbes ranked him seventh in the top 10 highest paid YouTubers in the Czech Republic with an estimated annual income of CZK 6 million. Kovy has published 2 books. The first is called Of course, the second is called iPohádka. In the first book he admitted to being gay. In 2019, he performed in the 10th season of the TV dance competition StarDance …when the stars dance, where he dropped out in the semi-finals. He placed 4th overall. He danced together with Veronika Liskova. Kovy currently has four YouTube channels. Call Me Charlie - 56k subscribers \n4. Best Moments - 13.6k subscribers His most watched video to date is a parody of the song Despacito, which has exceeded 12 million views. Kovy is very involved in politics, environmentalism, equality and education. In 2020, for example, he had a documentary Kovy Solves History on the TV station CT2. Kovy\'s Instagram profile (kovy_gameballcz) has more than 776,000 followers and contains more than 1,090 posts
